      "frameId": "f-3",
      "visualKind": "text",
      "title": "<p>This is a career development exercise based on <a href=\"https://designingyour.life/insights/the-magic-of-odysseys-prototyping-your-future-with-designing-your-life/\">Odyssey Planning from the Designing Your Life</a> book and template that also uses Miro Flows to help you progress forward. This is adapted to a career development scope.</p><p><br /></p><p>Each frame represents a plan for your career. The first is Plan A. This is the expected path, how things will go if you stay on your current trajectory.</p><p><br /></p><p>The second is Plan B. What would happen if you had to do something different from Plan A?<br /><br />The third is the Blue Sky path. What if you could have any path you want and limitations weren&#39;t a factor?</p><p><br /></p><p>On sticky notes, write details of the plan for the most immediate time frame and a few years later. Reflect on your sticky notes to answer the questions below each frame.</p><p><br /></p><p>When you&#39;re done, run the flow to generate summaries and next questions to contemplate. You can add any context you want to this board and connect it to the flow to enhance your summary and next steps. Thought starters of what to add:</p><p><br /></p><ol><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\"></span>Manager and peer feedback and reviews</li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\"></span>DISC or 16 Personalities assessment results</li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\"></span>Career role models and examples you aspire to<br /><br /><br /></li></ol>"
    },
